<br>
First: Test of patience (I soloed it at 25) test takes about 45min. Do turn in and wait 25-30min Lev to loc, cast invis to anamials, head to loc, wait few more min. Get arrow and do turn in, then gate.<br>
<br>
Second: Get a tracker for the wandering Spirit in WK, good luck without one.<br>
<br>
Third: Pages Drop Random off any mob in COM, Exception is students log (Only off courier in the stables, and not every times (1 in 4 is my expierience) Great place for exp for a group of lvl 40's or a pair of lvl 50's. <br>
<br>
Forth: Dire is a gimp, can be soloed EASILY with lvl 55 pet and KEI (Optional) I have soloed him 10 times at least and many lvl 20 shaman that were hunting in the zone got stoked. <br>
<br>
Last: Tear is looted AFTER killing one of tyhe golems on fear (named Terror, Hate, Fear i think). This is the bottle Neck however it can be MQed, the person(Shaman) doing the turn in MUST have proper True Spirit faction (Should have epic already) or this WILL NOT WORK (He Will not aggro on turn in and killing him will not result in the Iksar Scale). <br>
<br>
THE ENTIRE EPIC CAN BE BY-PASSED by looting the item droped in COM after turning in the Tear (Iksar Scale). However the true Spirit in EJ will not talk to you and will eat your epic item turn in if you are not of ALLY faction. The point to all the previous steps in the epic is to BUILD FACTION. I believe (Have not proven it) you can repeat many of the simple first steps in the epic to build fation to Max Ally and then MQ the turn in. (for example Run to BB kill peg-leg, get gem from true spirit, turn in to drunk shaman in NFP, Repeat about 100 times. The farther into the epic you do the repeats the more faction you get per attempt. (Killing dire and turning in pelt in EJ is a easy faction booster, if you can solo him)<br>
<br>
If anyone has specific questions about it post here and i'll see if i can answer them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub27.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stalkyrweaksoul>Stalkyr Weaksoul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:orange;'>Tavern Resident</span></span><br>  Posts: 735<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(2/4/03 9:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=17>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Shaman Myth's Revealed</span><hr size=1> Seeing how my shaman has bypassed all of the epic, I would like to correct some things you mentioned Ryverwin.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I believe (Have not proven it) you can repeat many of the simple first steps in the epic to build fation to Max Ally and then MQ the turn in. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The easist way is the part in Rathe Mountains and keep turning it in to the wandering spirit. I bought up a bunch of Woe and Envy and Marr's Promise and kept turning them in. About 12 maxed my faction (cost me ~1,000 pp).<br>
<br>
I got it MQ'd, but if I remember correctly Ranak's faction got dropped to Indifferent, when turning it in to the Spirit in EJ. So just because someone has an epic does not mean they can MQ it.<br>
<br>
So even if the shaman has epic, make sure they have the appropiate faction. <p>[65 Deceiver] <A HREF=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=530187>Marauder Stalkyr Weaksoul</A> [Mystic Valor]<BR>[59 Preserver] <A HREF=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=137325>Nytwolf Partywolf</A> [Mystic Valor]</p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#6FB8DD>- </font><a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern>The Saryrn Tavern</a><font color=#6FB8DD> - </font><a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernfrm9>Class Epic Quests</a><font color=#6FB8DD> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.246f<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

